cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, and specifically focuses on RGB-Infrared cross-modality matching. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel end-to-end model that uses generative adversarial networks (GANs) for joint pixel and feature alignment. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses two standard benchmarks for evaluation, which indicates that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves feature representation learning, which is a common topic in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with infrared images, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
